No , In java we cannot catch "Exception" before "NullPointerException" in a multi catch chain , 
because of how exception hierarchy works.

Why ?
Because NullPointerException is a subclass of Runtime Exception , which is a subclass of exception.

If we write :
try 
{
} 
catch (Exception e) 
{
    System.out.println("exception");
} 
catch (NullPointerException e) {
    System.out.println("Null pointer");
}

This will cause compile time error , because java won't allow it . 
Exception already catches all the exception including NullPointerException.
So the second catch block becomes unreachable 

Error to be faced: Unreachable catch block for NullPointerException

Rule here should be :
child exception then parent exception 